As required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process
When they believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect their rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request
With their trusted services providers who work on their behalf, do not have an independent use of the information we disclose to them, and have agreed to adhere to the rules set forth in this privacy statement

Opt-Out Rights

You can stop all collection of information by the Application easily by uninstalling it. You may use the standard uninstall processes as may be available as part of your mobile device or via the mobile application marketplace or network.

To cancel subscriptions and stop future payments, you must cancel your subscription through the Google Play Store following their standard cancellation procedures. Uninstalling the Application does not automatically cancel your subscription.

Data Retention Policy

The Service Provider will retain User Provided data for as long as you use the Application and for a reasonable time thereafter. If you'd like them to delete User Provided Data that you have provided via the Application, please contact them at guptanirbhay897@gmail.com and they will respond in a reasonable time.

Payment Data: As the Service Provider does not collect or store payment information, they cannot delete payment data. Any requests regarding payment data must be directed to Google Play Store or your payment service provider.

Children

The Application is rated for users aged 3+ and may be used by children under the supervision of parents or legal guardians.

The Service Provider does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13 years of age without parental consent. In the case the Service Provider discovers that a child under 13 has provided personal information without proper parental consent, the Service Provider will immediately delete this from their servers.

Parental Supervision: Parents or legal guardians are responsible for:

Supervising their child's use of the Application
Authorizing any subscription purchases made by minors
Managing payment methods accessible to minors through their Google Play Store account
Monitoring any charges incurred by minors

If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information or made unauthorized purchases, please contact the Service Provider at guptanirbhay897@gmail.com so that they will be able to take the necessary actions.

Security

The Service Provider is concerned about safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. The Service Provider provides physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect information the Service Provider processes and maintains.

Payment Security: While the Service Provider implements security measures for the Application, all payment security is the responsibility of Google Play Store and their payment processors. The Service Provider cannot guarantee the security of payment transactions as they are processed by third parties.

Changes

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. The Service Provider will notify you of any changes to the Privacy Policy by updating this page with the new Privacy Policy. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is deemed approval of all changes.

Your Consent

By using the Application, you are consenting to the processing of your information as set forth in this Privacy Policy now and as amended by us.

By subscribing to paid services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood the payment processing and fraud disclaimer sections of this Privacy Policy, and you agree to hold the Service Provider harmless from any payment-related issues.

Contact Us

